  <span class="title">WHO ARE WE?</span>
  <p>
    The ACM Web Organization is a branch of the Association for Computing
    Machinery (ACM), dedicated to exploring the role of technology in web
    development. Our mission is to help members learn essential web development
    skills, including front-end and back-end development, through hands-on
    experiences.
    <br />
    <br />
    We go beyond classroom learning by teaching programming languages like JavaScript
    and providing opportunities to apply these skills in interactive, team-based
    projects and competitions. Each year, we host a <b
      >Personal Website Competition</b
    >, where participants can showcase their abilities and gain experience
    creating tangible, professional-quality projects. Whether you're new to web
    development or looking to deepen your expertise, ACM Web is here to support
    your journey.
  </p>
